term: Format for pre/co reqs/never taken courses: requirements are comma seperated, if a group of courses is enclosed in brackets, any course enclosed can be used to satisfy that particular requirement.  Prereq is a course that has been taken previously to enrollment, coreq is a course that has either been taken previously or is being taken concurrently to enrollment, never taken requirements include course not previously taken and not currently enrolled.  Courses must specify semester because sections and class nbr reused in different semesters.
